<ol><li><b>Measure the diameter</b>&nbsp;of the wire&nbsp;\(d\)&nbsp;using a&nbsp;<b>micrometer</b>&nbsp;at several different points along the wire.<br></li><li><b>Calculate the cross-sectional area&nbsp;</b>\(A\)&nbsp;using the&nbsp;<b>mean value</b>&nbsp;of&nbsp;\(d\).<br></li><li><b>Measure the resistance</b>&nbsp;\(R\)&nbsp;of different lengths&nbsp;\(L\)&nbsp;of wire.<br></li><li><b>Plot a graph</b>&nbsp;of&nbsp;\(R\)&nbsp;against&nbsp;\(L\).<br></li></ol><div>The resistivity of the wire is given by</div><div>\[\text{graph gradient}\times A\]<br></div>